      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candles have all guttered out, and the silence of this house is more deafening than any scream. He is gone, and with him, the very light of my soul. I feel as though I am walking through a thick, cold fog, where every step is heavier than the last. There is no path forward, only this hollow, aching emptiness. It feels as though the world has simply ceased to want me.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
